value.value: Process of the sphenotic. The process may project antero-laterally or laterally or ventro-laterally and it has different development in different fish groups. The sphenotic spine is paired.
Superficial and lateral bony projection anterior to orbital region. Sometimes with superficial ornamentation where in direct contact with skin.

definition.value: Synonym of lateral ethmoid wing: lateral ethmoid ventral wing (characiforms).

value.value: Sensory canal on trunk which is posterior to the pectoral girdle and often reaching to or onto the caudal fin. The trunk sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

definition.value: Pores frequently piercing scales if present; occasionally enclosed in bony ossicles.

value.value: Sensory canal between and in close proximity to the trunk sensory canal and anteriorly with the otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals. The post-otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

definition.value: May be continuous with to the trunk sensory canal and anteriorly with the otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals.

value.value: Anatomical cluster that consists of a bulla formed by the exoccipital and basioccipital bones, and surrounds the lagena.
Multi-tissue structure composed of enameloid and dentine surrounding a pulp cavity, and found either attached to dermal bone or freely in the skin.
Odontode that is attached to dermal bone.
Odontode that is attached to the skin and without association to dermal bone.
Tooth that is attached to the premaxilla.

Sensory canal between and in close proximity posteriorly with the post-otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals, and anteriorly with the supraorbital and infraorbital sensory canals. The otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

definition.value: May be continuous with the post-otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals, and anteriorly with the supraorbital and infraorbital sensory canals.

value.value: Sensory canal that crosses over the dorsal midline and in close proximity to the contralateral post-otic sensory canals. The supratemporal sensory canal is unpaired.
Tooth that is attached to the ectopterygoid bone.
Tooth that is attached to the entopterygoid bone.
Most anterior pharyngobranchial cartilage, located medial to the epibranchials.
Most anterior pharyngobranchial bone, located medial to the epibranchials.
Most posterior pharyngobranchial bone, located medial to the epibranchials.
Perichordal bone that surrounds the anterior tip of the notochord.
Dermal bone of the pharyngeal arches usually bearing teeth.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies dorsal to the basihyal cartilage or bone.
Tooth that is attached to the basihyal tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 2 bone.
Tooth that is attached to the pharyngobranchial 2 tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 3 bone.
Tooth that is part of the pharyngobranchial 3 tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4, and located anterior to upper pharyngeal 5 tooth plate.
Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal 4 tooth plate.
Pharyngeal toothplate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4, and located posterior to upper pharyngeal 4 tooth plate.
Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal 5 tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchials 3 and 4.

definition.value: This represents the condition found in catfishes.

value.value: Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal tooth plate.
Tooth that is part of the basibranchial tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies dorsal to basibranchials 1-3.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies dorsal to basibranchial 4 bone.
Tooth that is attached to the basibranchial 4 tooth plate.
Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies dorsal to basibranchial 2 bone.
Tooth that is attached to the basibranchial 2 tooth plate.
Neural arch on the urostyle. It does not support a neural spine. Sanger and McCune 2002.
Anal fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.
Dorsal fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.
Infraorbital that is the sixth bone of the infraorbital series.

Bony projection that extends from the mesethmoid anteriorly. Mesethmoid cornua are paired processes each articulating with its ipsilateral premaxilla and both cornua bounding a median mesethmoid cleft.
Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and premaxilla. Mesethmoid-premaxillary joint is paired.
Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and nasal. Mesethmoid-nasal joint is paired.
Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and frontal. Mesethmoid-frontal joint is paired.
Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and lateral ethmoid. Mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.
Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and vomer. Mesethmoid-vomer joint is unpaired.
Bony projection that is mesially-directed and off the anteromedial corner of each mesethmoid cornu.
Ligament that is attached to supracleithrum and basioccipital.
Membrane bone that is fused to supracleithrum and is jointed to basioccipital and exoccipital.
Lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the ectopterygoid.
